<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<div type="elementDocumentation" xml:id="elem-label" xmlns:ead="http://ead3.archivists.org/schema/" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
               <head>
                  <gi>label</gi>
               </head>
               <div type="fullName">
                  <p xml:lang="eng">Label</p>
               </div>
               <div type="summary">
                  <p>A required child element of <gi>defitem</gi> that identifies the term or concept being defined or described.</p>
               </div>
               <div type="mayContain">
                  <p>[text], abbr, emph, expan, foreign, lb, ptr, ref</p>
               </div>
               <div type="mayOccurWithin">
                  <p>defitem</p>
               </div>
               <div type="attributes">
                  <p>
                     <list type="gloss">
                        <label>altrender</label>
                        <item>Optional</item>
                        <label>audience</label>
                        <item>Optional (values limited to: external, internal)</item>
                        <label>id</label>
                        <item>Optional</item>
                        <label>lang</label>
                        <item>Optional</item>
                        <label>script</label>
                        <item>Optional</item>
                     </list>
                  </p>
               </div>
               <div type="description">
                  <p>In a definition list, <gi>label</gi> and <gi>item</gi> are paired within <gi>defitem</gi>. <gi>label</gi> provides a term or concept that is then defined, described, or explained in an <gi>item</gi>.
                     A definition list is often displayed in two columns.</p>
               </div>
               <div type="seealso">
                  <list type="simple">
                     <item>Do not confuse with <att>label</att>, available on children of <gi>did</gi>, which allows the encoder to provide identifying information for public display.</item>
                  </list>
               </div>
               <div type="availability">
                  <p>Required, not repeatable</p>
               </div>
               
               <div type="examples">
                  <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" xml:lang="eng" valid="true">
                     <ead:list listtype="deflist">
                        <ead:defitem>
                           <ead:label>ALS</ead:label>
                           <ead:item>Autograph Letter Signed</ead:item>
                        </ead:defitem>
                        <ead:defitem>
                           <ead:label>TLS</ead:label>
                           <ead:item>Typewritten Letter Signed</ead:item>
                        </ead:defitem>
                     </ead:list>
                  </egXML>
               </div>
            </div>